	(7962,113,'challenge_content','<p class=\"tb f5\"><span class=\"tx\">72% of new users dropped off (and never converted) after clicking</span><span class=\"tx f14\"> </span><span class=\"tx f910\">a prominent “Buy Now”</span><span class=\"tx f910\">button on our client’s homepage. Our challenge was to understand what was occurring and</span></p><p class=\"tb f5\"><span class=\"tx\">improve the drop off.</span></p>'),
	(7963,113,'solution_header','Solution:'),
	(7964,113,'solution_content','<p class=\"tb f5\"><span class=\"tx\">We analyzed user pathways in Analytics and determined the location of conversion </span><span class=\"tx f910\">“bottlenecking”. We devised a va</span><span class=\"tx\">riety of advanced site testing campaigns designed to reveal the </span>top performing conversion page(s). </p>'),
	(7965,113,'results_header','Results:'),
	(7966,113,'results_content','<p><span class=\"tx\">Through analysis and A/B site testing we were able improve conversion rate of new users </span><span class=\"tx f910\">clicking “Buy now” by 25%</span><span class=\"tx\"> and add-to-cart rate by 43%. The insights gained through landing </span><span class=\"tx\">page tests further benefit future optimization on the site and will fold into long term strategy for </span><span class=\"tx\">growing direct traffic sales. </span></p>'),
	(7967,113,'case_study_image_url','case-study-cro.jpg'),
	(7968,113,'background_image','cs-cro.jpg'),
